{"title_page": "Polaroid (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 American supernatural horror film}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Polaroid\n| image          = Polaroid teaser poster.jpg\n| caption        = German theatrical release poster\n| director       = Lars Klevberg\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Roy Lee]]\n* Chris Bender\n* Michael Mahoney\n}}\n| screenplay     = [[Blair Butler]]\n| based on       = {{based on|''Polaroid''|Lars Klevberg}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Kathryn Prescott]]\n* [[Grace Zabriskie]]\n* [[Samantha Logan]]\n* [[Tyler Young (actor)|Tyler Young]]\n* [[Javier Botet]]\n* [[Katie Stevens]]\n* [[Madelaine Petsch]]\n* Priscilla Quintana\n* [[Davi Santos]]\n* Keenan Tracey\n* [[Mitch Pileggi]]\n}}\n| cinematography = P\u00e5l Ulvik Rokseth\n| music          = Philip Giffin\n| editing        = Peter Gvozdas\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Dimension Films]]\n* Benderspink\n* Eldorado Film\n* [[Vertigo Entertainment]]\n}}\n| distributor    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Vertical Entertainment]] (United States)\n* [[Lantern Entertainment]] (International co-distribution with 13 Films)\n}}\n| released       = {{film date|2019|1|10|Germany|2019|9|17|United States}}\n| runtime        = 88 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| gross          = $2.4 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/releasegroup/gr2311803397/?landingModalImageUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fm.media-amazon.com%2Fimages%2FG%2F01%2FIMDbPro%2Fimages%2Fhome%2FwelcomeToBomojov2._CB1571421611_.png|title=Polaroid|website=Box Office Mojo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Polaroid-(2019)|title=Polaroid (2019) - Financial Information|website=The Numbers}}</ref>   \n}}\n\n'''''Polaroid''''' is a 2019 American [[supernatural horror film]] directed by Lars Klevberg, and based on his 2015 short film of the same name. In the film, high schooler Bird Fitcher finds a vintage Polaroid camera that holds dark and mysterious secrets. She soon realizes that those who get their picture taken by it meet a tragic death. It stars [[Kathryn Prescott]], [[Samantha Logan]], [[Tyler Young (actor)|Tyler Young]], and [[Javier Botet]].\n\n[[Dimension Films]] announced the film in 2015, with Klevberg set to direct and Blair Butler writing the script. [[Principal photography]]\u00a0began in\u00a0[[Halifax, Nova Scotia]] on March 9, 2017, and was completed in May 2017. The film was originally set to be released in August 2017, but was rescheduled several times. By October 2018, [[Lantern Entertainment]], which acquired [[The Weinstein Company]]/Dimension's assets through its bankruptcy, and 13 Films, an international distribution and finance company, had struck a deal to co-distribute the film internationally.\n\nPolaroid was theatrically released in Germany on January 10, 2019, by Wild Bunch, and in the United Kingdom on June 1, 2019. It was released in the United States on September 17, 2019, in select theatres and on VOD, by [[Vertical Entertainment]], before streaming on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ihorror.com/long-awaited-polaroid-will-finally-be-released-in-september/|title=Long-Awaited 'Polaroid' will Finally be Released in September|first=Waylon|last=Jordan|date=August 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://1428elm.com/2020/02/16/polaroid-3-reasons/|title=3 Reasons Netflix\u2019s Polaroid is a must watch horror film|date=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThis MoVIE IS NOT DEMONICSarah and her friend are going through a box of her late mother's stuff when they find a Polaroid camera. The friend received a \u201clike\u201d from her crush, which provokes Sarah to take a photo in lingerie on the Polaroid camera. When the flash goes off, Sarah seems uneasy. Her friend leaves, and Sarah is home alone. When she takes a look at the Polaroid, there is a creepy shadow behind her in the photo of her. Startled, she treats it as a smudge and starts cleaning. She hears eerie sounds in the attic, which she investigates. She gets frightened in the attic and falls, but ends up dangling by her ankles instead of falling to the floor. While feeling a brief moment of relief as her hair dangles in her face, she is then pulled up by an entity and is killed offscreen before her dead body tumbles to the ground.\n\nShy high school student Bird is given an old [[Polaroid camera]] by her co-worker Tyler, who got it from a garage sale. The camera has the initials \u201cRJS\u201d carved into it. Bird snaps a picture of Tyler but later notices an odd smudge-like figure on his photo.\n\nBird attends a costume party with her best friend Kasey and meets her other friends Mina, Mina's boyfriend Devin, Avery, and Bird's high school crush Connor. She uses her Polaroid camera to take the group's picture and Avery later snaps a selfie with it. Meanwhile, Tyler is killed by the entity, and Sheriff Pembroke informs Bird. At home, Bird sees Tyler's photo free from the shadow, which has mysteriously transferred to Avery's photo.\n\nAvery is killed when the entity snaps her neck. When Bird learns about this, she tries to destroy the camera and attempts to warn her friends. Devin attempts to burn the group photo, but when the flames reach Mina in the photo, her arm spontaneously combusts and the flames cannot be extinguished. Kasey's fingers are slightly singed before Bird stomps out the fire and the photograph restores itself. Mina is taken to the hospital to undergo surgery for her arm; Devin and Kasey stay with her while Bird and Connor leave to learn more about the camera. Bird and Connor research and discover that the camera was owned by a photography teacher Roland Joseph Sable (RJS) from their school years ago. He was accused of torturing four students and killing three of them while taking maniacal photographs. One of the captives escaped and Roland was killed by police. Bird is attacked by the entity, which behaves like a photograph: following the same rules as photographic development (i.e. it is sensitive to heat). She questions why she was chased too and notices that her reflection is in the photo's background. \n\nMina is killed at the hospital by the entity when she is left alone briefly. Devin finds Mina's dead body and blames Bird for her death. Devin confronts Bird at the diner and accuses her of being responsible for what happened to Mina. He attempts to take a picture of her as a threat. With Connor and Devin both fighting for the camera, Devin is accidentally snapped by the camera and the shadow transfers to his photo, showing he is next. Devin lunges at Bird, Kasey saves Bird by stabbing Devin's photo with a pencil, injuring him in real life. Devin upset from being stabbed becomes aggressive and accidentally slaps a sheriff named Pembroke. Devin is detained and is later killed in his cell by the entity.\n\nConnor, Kasey, and Bird learn Roland's wife is alive and visit her. They meet an elderly lady named Lena Sable, who explains that the camera actually belonged to her daughter Rebecca Jane Sable (RJS). Lena explains that Rebecca was \"slow,\" and when gifted with the camera she became very attached to it. As a result, Rebecca was bullied by four classmates, who took the camera and used it to take inappropriate photos of her. She committed suicide out of shame, causing her father Roland to abduct and kill her bullies in a fit of rage. Now even in death, Roland roams, looking for the last bully who escaped to kill him. Lena shows the two a picture of the survivor and they search the yearbooks. Bird finds out that the survivor was Sheriff Pembroke. In an attempt to stop the entity from killing them, Connor takes a picture of Pembroke, who reveals that Roland was the real bully to Rebecca, having sexually assaulted her. The four students, including him, were Rebecca's friends trying to warn her of her father's actions upon finding her nude pictures in his possession. Fearing the public would find out, Roland abducted them, prompting Rebecca to kill herself in fear. \n\nThe entity tears Pembroke's picture in half, killing him. The entity stabs through Kasey's leg, impairing her ability to walk. Connor is separated from Kasey and Bird; the girls find safety in the school's showers, with Bird turning on the hot water to create heat, preventing the entity from reaching them. Bird leaves to find Connor, they reunite and she has an idea that involves getting the camera back (having been left where Sheriff Pembroke was killed) and going somewhere where the entity can \"fully develop.\" The entity manifests and drags Connor away, but Bird takes a picture of herself, prompting the creature to chase after her. She leads the entity into the school's dark room, where it is able to fully develop. She takes a picture of the entity, crushes the photo trying to kill it. Unsuccessful and fearing for her life she then burns it last minute, disintegrating the entity where everything took place many years ago. She reunites with her friends and throws the camera into a river.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Kathryn Prescott]] as Bird Fitcher\n* [[Tyler Young (actor)|Tyler Young]] as Connor Bell\n* [[Samantha Logan]] as Kasey Walters\n* Keenan Tracey as Devin Lane\n* Priscilla Quintana as Mina Rodriguez\n* [[Javier Botet]] as The Entity\n* [[Mitch Pileggi]] as Thomas Pembroke\n* [[Katie Stevens]] as Avery Bishop\n* [[Davi Santos]] as Tyler Drew\n* [[Shauna MacDonald]] as Mrs. Fitcher \n* [[Grace Zabriskie]] as Lena Sable\n* Rhys Bevan John as Roland Joseph Sable\n* Emily Power as Rebecca Sable\n* [[Madelaine Petsch]] as Sarah Dawson\n* Erika Prevost as Linda Vu\n\n==Production==\n[[Dimension Films]] spearheaded the feature, an adaptation of the 2015 short film ''Polaroid'', written and directed by Norwegian director Lars Klevberg, who also directed the full length version. Chris Bender, Jake Weiner and Jake Wagner produced with Benderspink, [[Roy Lee]] with Vertigo and Petter Onstad L\u00f8kke and John Einar Hagen with Eldorado Film, which had produced the short film with Klevberg in Norway.{{Citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began in [[Halifax, Nova Scotia]] on March 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/polaroid-dimension-film-bob-weinstein-grudge-ring-1202005546/|title=Dimension Films Begins Production on Horror Film 'Polaroid'|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 9, 2017|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film was originally scheduled to be released on August 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3416697/dimension-snaps-polaroid-next-august/|title=Dimension Snaps a 'Polaroid' Next August|website=[[Bloody-Disgusting.com]]|first=Brad|last=Miska|date=December 2, 2017|accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref> It was then pushed back to December 1, 2017, before being moved up to November 22, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/10/polaroid-horror-film-thanksgiving-release-1202182212/|title=Dimension Horror Movie 'Polaroid' To Make Memories Over Thanksgiving Stretch|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=October 4, 2017|accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref> It was then pulled from the schedule, with plans to release the film in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jenna Busch|url=https://comingsoon.net/movies/news/899721-weinstein-co-dimensions-horror-film-polaroid-moves-to-2018#/slide/1|title=Weinstein Co./Dimension's Horror Film Polaroid Moves to 2018|website=ComingSoon|date=October 31, 2017|accessdate=October 31, 2017}}</ref> [[Vertical Entertainment]] acquired distribution rights to the film, and released it on September 17, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstshowing.net/2019/surprise-new-trailer-for-long-lost-deadly-camera-horror-film-polaroid/|title=Surprise New Trailer for Long Lost Deadly Camera Horror 'Polaroid'|website=First Showing|first=Alex|last=Billington|date=August 20, 2019|accessdate=August 20, 2019}}</ref> As of 2020, the film streams on [[Netflix]].\n\nIn October 2018, [[Lantern Entertainment]], which acquired [[The Weinstein Company]]'s assets through its bankruptcy, including Dimension Films content; and 13 Films, an international distribution and finance company, struck a deal to co-distribute ''Polaroid'' internationally.<ref>{{cite news|last=Vlessing|first=Etan|date=October 8, 2018|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/benedict-cumberbatchs-current-war-get-international-release-1150266|title=Benedict Cumberbatch's 'The Current War' to Get International Release|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=October 20, 2018}}</ref> The film was theatrically released in Germany on January 10, 2019, by [[Wild Bunch (company)|Wild Bunch]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmstarts.de/kritiken/242004.html|title=Polaroid \u2013 Film 2019|website=Filmstarts.de|language=German|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref> The film was released in the United Kingdom on June 1, 2019.{{cn|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe film has a rating 0% on [[Rotten Tomatoes]] based on 5 reviews.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/polaroid_2019|title=Polaroid (2019)|via=www.rottentomatoes.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|5598292}}\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|polaroid_2017|Polaroid}}\n*{{Metacritic film|id=polaroid|title=Polaroid}}\n\n[[Category:2019 horror films]]\n[[Category:2010s supernatural films]]\n[[Category:2010s teen horror films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American supernatural horror films]]\n[[Category:American teen horror films]]\n[[Category:Cameras in fiction]]\n[[Category:Dimension Films films]]\n[[Category:Demons in film]]\n[[Category:Features based on short films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Vertical Entertainment films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 American supernatural horror film}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Polaroid\n| image          = Polaroid teaser poster.jpg\n| caption        = German theatrical release poster\n| director       = Lars Klevberg\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Roy Lee]]\n* Chris Bender\n* Michael Mahoney\n}}\n| screenplay     = [[Blair Butler]]\n| based on       = {{based on|''Polaroid''|Lars Klevberg}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Kathryn Prescott]]\n* [[Grace Zabriskie]]\n* [[Samantha Logan]]\n* [[Tyler Young (actor)|Tyler Young]]\n* [[Javier Botet]]\n* [[Katie Stevens]]\n* [[Madelaine Petsch]]\n* Priscilla Quintana\n* [[Davi Santos]]\n* Keenan Tracey\n* [[Mitch Pileggi]]\n}}\n| cinematography = P\u00e5l Ulvik Rokseth\n| music          = Philip Giffin\n| editing        = Peter Gvozdas\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Dimension Films]]\n* Benderspink\n* Eldorado Film\n* [[Vertigo Entertainment]]\n}}\n| distributor    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Vertical Entertainment]] (United States)\n* [[Lantern Entertainment]] (International co-distribution with 13 Films)\n}}\n| released       = {{film date|2019|1|10|Germany|2019|9|17|United States}}\n| runtime        = 88 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| gross          = $2.4 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/releasegroup/gr2311803397/?landingModalImageUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fm.media-amazon.com%2Fimages%2FG%2F01%2FIMDbPro%2Fimages%2Fhome%2FwelcomeToBomojov2._CB1571421611_.png|title=Polaroid|website=Box Office Mojo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Polaroid-(2019)|title=Polaroid (2019) - Financial Information|website=The Numbers}}</ref>   \n}}\n\n'''''Polaroid''''' is a 2019 American [[supernatural horror film]] directed by Lars Klevberg, and based on his 2015 short film of the same name. In the film, high schooler Bird Fitcher finds a vintage Polaroid camera that holds dark and mysterious secrets. She soon realizes that those who get their picture taken by it meet a tragic death. It stars [[Kathryn Prescott]], [[Samantha Logan]], [[Tyler Young (actor)|Tyler Young]], and [[Javier Botet]].\n\n[[Dimension Films]] announced the film in 2015, with Klevberg set to direct and Blair Butler writing the script. [[Principal photography]]\u00a0began in\u00a0[[Halifax, Nova Scotia]] on March 9, 2017, and was completed in May 2017. The film was originally set to be released in August 2017, but was rescheduled several times. By October 2018, [[Lantern Entertainment]], which acquired [[The Weinstein Company]]/Dimension's assets through its bankruptcy, and 13 Films, an international distribution and finance company, had struck a deal to co-distribute the film internationally.\n\nPolaroid was theatrically released in Germany on January 10, 2019, by Wild Bunch, and in the United Kingdom on June 1, 2019. It was released in the United States on September 17, 2019, in select theatres and on VOD, by [[Vertical Entertainment]], before streaming on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ihorror.com/long-awaited-polaroid-will-finally-be-released-in-september/|title=Long-Awaited 'Polaroid' will Finally be Released in September|first=Waylon|last=Jordan|date=August 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://1428elm.com/2020/02/16/polaroid-3-reasons/|title=3 Reasons Netflix\u2019s Polaroid is a must watch horror film|date=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nSarah and her friend are going through a box of her late mother's stuff when they find a Polaroid camera. The friend received a \u201clike\u201d from her crush, which provokes Sarah to take a photo in lingerie on the Polaroid camera. When the flash goes off, Sarah seems uneasy. Her friend leaves, and Sarah is home alone. When she takes a look at the Polaroid, there is a creepy shadow behind her in the photo of her. Startled, she treats it as a smudge and starts cleaning. She hears eerie sounds in the attic, which she investigates. She gets frightened in the attic and falls, but ends up dangling by her ankles instead of falling to the floor. While feeling a brief moment of relief as her hair dangles in her face, she is then pulled up by an entity and is killed offscreen before her dead body tumbles to the ground.\n\nShy high school student Bird is given an old [[Polaroid camera]] by her co-worker Tyler, who got it from a garage sale. The camera has the initials \u201cRJS\u201d carved into it. Bird snaps a picture of Tyler but later notices an odd smudge-like figure on his photo.\n\nBird attends a costume party with her best friend Kasey and meets her other friends Mina, Mina's boyfriend Devin, Avery, and Bird's high school crush Connor. She uses her Polaroid camera to take the group's picture and Avery later snaps a selfie with it. Meanwhile, Tyler is killed by the entity, and Sheriff Pembroke informs Bird. At home, Bird sees Tyler's photo free from the shadow, which has mysteriously transferred to Avery's photo.\n\nAvery is killed when the entity snaps her neck. When Bird learns about this, she tries to destroy the camera and attempts to warn her friends. Devin attempts to burn the group photo, but when the flames reach Mina in the photo, her arm spontaneously combusts and the flames cannot be extinguished. Kasey's fingers are slightly singed before Bird stomps out the fire and the photograph restores itself. Mina is taken to the hospital to undergo surgery for her arm; Devin and Kasey stay with her while Bird and Connor leave to learn more about the camera. Bird and Connor research and discover that the camera was owned by a photography teacher Roland Joseph Sable (RJS) from their school years ago. He was accused of torturing four students and killing three of them while taking maniacal photographs. One of the captives escaped and Roland was killed by police. Bird is attacked by the entity, which behaves like a photograph: following the same rules as photographic development (i.e. it is sensitive to heat). She questions why she was chased too and notices that her reflection is in the photo's background. \n\nMina is killed at the hospital by the entity when she is left alone briefly. Devin finds Mina's dead body and blames Bird for her death. Devin confronts Bird at the diner and accuses her of being responsible for what happened to Mina. He attempts to take a picture of her as a threat. With Connor and Devin both fighting for the camera, Devin is accidentally snapped by the camera and the shadow transfers to his photo, showing he is next. Devin lunges at Bird, Kasey saves Bird by stabbing Devin's photo with a pencil, injuring him in real life. Devin upset from being stabbed becomes aggressive and accidentally slaps a sheriff named Pembroke. Devin is detained and is later killed in his cell by the entity.\n\nConnor, Kasey, and Bird learn Roland's wife is alive and visit her. They meet an elderly lady named Lena Sable, who explains that the camera actually belonged to her daughter Rebecca Jane Sable (RJS). Lena explains that Rebecca was \"slow,\" and when gifted with the camera she became very attached to it. As a result, Rebecca was bullied by four classmates, who took the camera and used it to take inappropriate photos of her. She committed suicide out of shame, causing her father Roland to abduct and kill her bullies in a fit of rage. Now even in death, Roland roams, looking for the last bully who escaped to kill him. Lena shows the two a picture of the survivor and they search the yearbooks. Bird finds out that the survivor was Sheriff Pembroke. In an attempt to stop the entity from killing them, Connor takes a picture of Pembroke, who reveals that Roland was the real bully to Rebecca, having sexually assaulted her. The four students, including him, were Rebecca's friends trying to warn her of her father's actions upon finding her nude pictures in his possession. Fearing the public would find out, Roland abducted them, prompting Rebecca to kill herself in fear. \n\nThe entity tears Pembroke's picture in half, killing him. The entity stabs through Kasey's leg, impairing her ability to walk. Connor is separated from Kasey and Bird; the girls find safety in the school's showers, with Bird turning on the hot water to create heat, preventing the entity from reaching them. Bird leaves to find Connor, they reunite and she has an idea that involves getting the camera back (having been left where Sheriff Pembroke was killed) and going somewhere where the entity can \"fully develop.\" The entity manifests and drags Connor away, but Bird takes a picture of herself, prompting the creature to chase after her. She leads the entity into the school's dark room, where it is able to fully develop. She takes a picture of the entity, crushes the photo trying to kill it. Unsuccessful and fearing for her life she then burns it last minute, disintegrating the entity where everything took place many years ago. She reunites with her friends and throws the camera into a river.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Kathryn Prescott]] as Bird Fitcher\n* [[Tyler Young (actor)|Tyler Young]] as Connor Bell\n* [[Samantha Logan]] as Kasey Walters\n* Keenan Tracey as Devin Lane\n* Priscilla Quintana as Mina Rodriguez\n* [[Javier Botet]] as The Entity\n* [[Mitch Pileggi]] as Thomas Pembroke\n* [[Katie Stevens]] as Avery Bishop\n* [[Davi Santos]] as Tyler Drew\n* [[Shauna MacDonald]] as Mrs. Fitcher \n* [[Grace Zabriskie]] as Lena Sable\n* Rhys Bevan John as Roland Joseph Sable\n* Emily Power as Rebecca Sable\n* [[Madelaine Petsch]] as Sarah Dawson\n* Erika Prevost as Linda Vu\n\n==Production==\n[[Dimension Films]] spearheaded the feature, an adaptation of the 2015 short film ''Polaroid'', written and directed by Norwegian director Lars Klevberg, who also directed the full length version. Chris Bender, Jake Weiner and Jake Wagner produced with Benderspink, [[Roy Lee]] with Vertigo and Petter Onstad L\u00f8kke and John Einar Hagen with Eldorado Film, which had produced the short film with Klevberg in Norway.{{Citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began in [[Halifax, Nova Scotia]] on March 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/polaroid-dimension-film-bob-weinstein-grudge-ring-1202005546/|title=Dimension Films Begins Production on Horror Film 'Polaroid'|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 9, 2017|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film was originally scheduled to be released on August 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3416697/dimension-snaps-polaroid-next-august/|title=Dimension Snaps a 'Polaroid' Next August|website=[[Bloody-Disgusting.com]]|first=Brad|last=Miska|date=December 2, 2017|accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref> It was then pushed back to December 1, 2017, before being moved up to November 22, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/10/polaroid-horror-film-thanksgiving-release-1202182212/|title=Dimension Horror Movie 'Polaroid' To Make Memories Over Thanksgiving Stretch|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=October 4, 2017|accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref> It was then pulled from the schedule, with plans to release the film in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jenna Busch|url=https://comingsoon.net/movies/news/899721-weinstein-co-dimensions-horror-film-polaroid-moves-to-2018#/slide/1|title=Weinstein Co./Dimension's Horror Film Polaroid Moves to 2018|website=ComingSoon|date=October 31, 2017|accessdate=October 31, 2017}}</ref> [[Vertical Entertainment]] acquired distribution rights to the film, and released it on September 17, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstshowing.net/2019/surprise-new-trailer-for-long-lost-deadly-camera-horror-film-polaroid/|title=Surprise New Trailer for Long Lost Deadly Camera Horror 'Polaroid'|website=First Showing|first=Alex|last=Billington|date=August 20, 2019|accessdate=August 20, 2019}}</ref> As of 2020, the film streams on [[Netflix]].\n\nIn October 2018, [[Lantern Entertainment]], which acquired [[The Weinstein Company]]'s assets through its bankruptcy, including Dimension Films content; and 13 Films, an international distribution and finance company, struck a deal to co-distribute ''Polaroid'' internationally.<ref>{{cite news|last=Vlessing|first=Etan|date=October 8, 2018|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/benedict-cumberbatchs-current-war-get-international-release-1150266|title=Benedict Cumberbatch's 'The Current War' to Get International Release|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=October 20, 2018}}</ref> The film was theatrically released in Germany on January 10, 2019, by [[Wild Bunch (company)|Wild Bunch]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmstarts.de/kritiken/242004.html|title=Polaroid \u2013 Film 2019|website=Filmstarts.de|language=German|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref> The film was released in the United Kingdom on June 1, 2019.{{cn|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe film has a rating 0% on [[Rotten Tomatoes]] based on 5 reviews.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/polaroid_2019|title=Polaroid (2019)|via=www.rottentomatoes.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|5598292}}\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|polaroid_2017|Polaroid}}\n*{{Metacritic film|id=polaroid|title=Polaroid}}\n\n[[Category:2019 horror films]]\n[[Category:2010s supernatural films]]\n[[Category:2010s teen horror films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American supernatural horror films]]\n[[Category:American teen horror films]]\n[[Category:Cameras in fiction]]\n[[Category:Dimension Films films]]\n[[Category:Demons in film]]\n[[Category:Features based on short films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Vertical Entertainment films]]\n", "name_user": "2001:579:2444:64b0:e549:1bfc:5c2d:2380", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ePlot)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polaroid_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Julio Rico", "text_new": "{{spanish name|Rico|Pardillo}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Julio Rico\n| image =\n| fullname = Julio Alberto Rico Pardillo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|6|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[El Rubio]], Spain\n| height = {{convert|1.84|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]] / [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Burgos CF|Burgos]]\n| clubnumber =\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[\u00c9cija Balompi\u00e9|\u00c9cija]]\n| youthyears2 = 2001\u20132008 | youthclubs2 = [[Real Betis|Betis]]\n| years1 = 2008\u20132010 | clubs1 = [[Real Betis C|Betis C]] | caps1 = 31 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2008\u20132010 | clubs2 = [[Real Betis B|Betis B]] | caps2 = 4 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2010 | clubs3 = [[Real Madrid C]] | caps3 = 4 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2010\u20132011 | clubs4 = [[CF Pobla de Mafumet|Pobla Mafumet]] | caps4 = 33 | goals4 = 7\n| years5 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs5 = [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona|Gimn\u00e0stic]] | caps5 = 2 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2012 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[RCD Espanyol B|Espanyol B]] (loan) | caps6 = 11 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[CE L'Hospitalet|Hospitalet]] | caps7 = 34 | goals7 = 4\n| years8 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs8 = [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]] | caps8 = 28 | goals8 = 1\n| years9 = 2014\u20132017 | clubs9 = [[UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s|Logro\u00f1\u00e9s]] | caps9 = 67 | goals9 = 2\n| years10 = 2017\u2013 | clubs10 = [[Burgos CF|Burgos]] | caps10 = 62 | goals10 = 4\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals =  \n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 =\n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update =\n}}\n'''Julio Alberto Rico Pardillo''' (born 11 June 1989) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Burgos CF]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] or [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|right midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Early years===\nBorn in [[El Rubio]], [[Province of Seville]], Andalusia, Rico started playing with [[\u00c9cija Balompi\u00e9]]. In 2001 the 12-year-old moved to neighbouring [[Real Betis]], going on to finish his football formation there.\n\nIn the following two years, Rubio alternated between the club's [[Real Betis C|third]] and [[Real Betis B|second teams]], appearing in only four [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]] games with the latter in two seasons combined.\n\n===Real Madrid C===\nIn mid-February 2010, Rico signed with [[La Liga]] giants [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], being assigned to its [[Real Madrid C|C-team]].<ref>[http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/es/1202812988605/noticia/Noticia/Nuevo_refuerzo_para_el_Real_Madrid_C.htm Nuevo refuerzo para el Real Madrid C (New signing for Real Madrid C)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110915051434/http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/es/1202812988605/noticia/Noticia/Nuevo_refuerzo_para_el_Real_Madrid_C.htm|date=15 September 2011}}; Real Madrid CF, 18 February 2010 (in Spanish)</ref> During his four-month spell, he played just four [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] matches.\n\n===Gimn\u00e0stic===\nIn the summer of 2010, Rico signed with [[CF Pobla de Mafumet]] which acted as [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona]]'s [[farm team]], being first-choice with the fourth division side. In [[2010\u201311 Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|his first season]] he managed to be the former's third top scorer, behind [[Albert Virgili]] and [[Fran Carbi\u00e0]].\n\nOn 23 June 2011, Rico was promoted to ''N\u00e0stic'''s first team and signed a two-year contract.<ref>[http://www.nastictac.com/2011/06/julio-rico-pasa-a-ser-jugador-de-la-primera-plantilla-del-nastic/ Julio Rico pasa a ser jugador de la primera plantilla del N\u00e0stic (Julio Rico is now N\u00e0stic first-team player)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110702004803/http://www.nastictac.com/2011/06/julio-rico-pasa-a-ser-jugador-de-la-primera-plantilla-del-nastic/|date=2 July 2011}}; N\u00e0stic Tac, 23 June 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> On 10 July, he was officially presented by the [[Catalonia|Catalans]].<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2011/07/10/futbol/equipos/gimnastic/1310333141.html Julio Rico, presentado con el primer equipo (Julio Rico, presented with the first team)]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 10 July 2011 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nRico made his competitive debut with Gimn\u00e0stic on 6 August 2011, against [[RCD Espanyol]] for the season's [[Copa Catalunya]], coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] [[Berry Powel]] in the 64th minute of a 1\u20132 loss.<ref>[http://www.rcdespanyol.com/principal.php?modulo=detalleNoticia&idnoticia=11650&idseccion=28&idsite=1&idmenu=9&idsubmenu=108 2\u20131: Finalistes (2\u20131: Finalists)]; RCD Espanyol, 6 August 2011 (in Catalan)</ref> He made his first [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] appearance on 4 September, replacing [[Eloy Gila|Eloy]] in a 0\u20130 draw at [[CD Numancia]];<ref>[http://www.gimnasticdetarragona.com/cat2/es/act-noticia.php?id=4024 Numancia 0\u20130 N\u00e0stic]; Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona, 4 September 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> after only two league appearances (three overall), he was loaned to [[RCD Espanyol B]].<ref>[http://www.manquepierda.com/blog/el-ex-canterano-julio-rico-cedido-al-espanol-b-conoce-mas-sobre-el/ El ex canterano Julio Rico, cedido al Espa\u00f1ol B. Conoce m\u00e1s sobre \u00e9l (Former youth player Julio Rico, loaned to Espa\u00f1ol B. Learn more about him)]; Manquepierda, 31 January 2012 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\n===Journeyman===\nRico had his contract with Gimn\u00e0stic terminated on 31 August 2012.<ref>[http://www.gimnasticdetarragona.com/cat2/es/act-noticia.php?id=4953 El N\u00e0stic y Julio Rico rescinden el contrato (N\u00e0stic and Julio Rico terminate contract)]; Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona, 31 August 2012 (in Spanish)</ref> On the same day, he signed with [[CE L'Hospitalet]] also of the third level,<ref>[http://lasegundabarrabajab.blogspot.com.br/2012/08/julio-rico-ficha-por-el-hospitalet_31.html Julio Rico ficha por el Hospitalet (Julio Rico signs for Hospitalet)]; La Segunda B, 31 August 2012 (in Spanish)</ref> and on 20 August of the following year he joined fellow league club [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]].<ref>[http://www.todomercadoweb.es/mercado-futbolistico/oficial-cultural-leonesa-llega-julio-rico-54573 Oficial: Cultural Leonesa, llega Julio Rico (Official: Cultural Leonesa, Julio Rico arrives)]; Todo Mercado Web, 20 August 2013 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nOn 2 July 2014, Rico moved to [[UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s]] still in the third tier.<ref>[http://uniondeportivalogro\u00f1es.com/index.php/8-destacados/668-el-defensa-lateral-julio-rico-nuevo-jugador-de-la-ud-logrones El defensa lateral Julio Rico, nuevo jugador de la UD. Logro\u00f1\u00e9s (Full back Julio Rico, new player of UD. Logro\u00f1\u00e9s)]; UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s, 2 July 2014 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|400380}}\n*{{Futbolme profile|7085}}\n*{{LaPreferente|27613}}\n*[http://beticopedia.blogspot.com/2011/07/julio-rico.html Stats at Beticopedia] {{in lang|es}}\n*{{Soccerway|julio-alberto-rico-pardillo/205479}}\n\n{{Burgos CF squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rico, Julio}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Sierra Sur (Seville)]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Andalusian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Betis Deportivo Balompi\u00e9 footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid C footballers]]\n[[Category:CF Pobla de Mafumet footballers]]\n[[Category:Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona footballers]]\n[[Category:RCD Espanyol B footballers]]\n[[Category:CE L'Hospitalet players]]\n[[Category:Cultural Leonesa footballers]]\n[[Category:UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s players]]\n[[Category:Burgos CF footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{spanish name|Rico|Pardillo}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Julio Rico\n| image =\n| fullname = Julio Alberto Rico Pardillo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|6|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[El Rubio]], Spain\n| height = {{convert|1.84|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]] / [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Burgos CF|Burgos]]\n| clubnumber =\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[\u00c9cija Balompi\u00e9|\u00c9cija]]\n| youthyears2 = 2001\u20132008 | youthclubs2 = [[Real Betis|Betis]]\n| years1 = 2008\u20132010 | clubs1 = [[Real Betis C|Betis C]] | caps1 = 31 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2008\u20132010 | clubs2 = [[Real Betis B|Betis B]] | caps2 = 4 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2010 | clubs3 = [[Real Madrid C]] | caps3 = 4 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2010\u20132011 | clubs4 = [[CF Pobla de Mafumet|Pobla Mafumet]] | caps4 = 33 | goals4 = 7\n| years5 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs5 = [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona|Gimn\u00e0stic]] | caps5 = 2 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2012 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[RCD Espanyol B|Espanyol B]] (loan) | caps6 = 11 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[CE L'Hospitalet|Hospitalet]] | caps7 = 34 | goals7 = 4\n| years8 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs8 = [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]] | caps8 = 28 | goals8 = 1\n| years9 = 2014\u20132017 | clubs9 = [[UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s|Logro\u00f1\u00e9s]] | caps9 = 67 | goals9 = 2\n| years10 = 2017\u2013 | clubs10 = [[Burgos CF|Burgos]] | caps10 = 62 | goals10 = 4\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals =  \n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 =\n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update =\n}}\n'''Julio Alberto Rico Pardillo''' (born 11 June 1989) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Burgos CF]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] or [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|right midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Early years===\nBorn in [[El Rubio]], [[Province of Seville]], Andalusia, Rico started playing with [[\u00c9cija Balompi\u00e9]]. In 2001 the 12-year-old moved to neighbouring [[Real Betis]], going on to finish his football formation there.\n\nIn the following two years, Rubio alternated between the club's [[Real Betis C|third]] and [[Real Betis B|second teams]], appearing in only four [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]] games with the latter in two seasons combined.\n\n===Real Madrid C===\nIn mid-February 2010, Rico signed with [[La Liga]] giants [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], being assigned to its [[Real Madrid C|C-team]].<ref>[http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/es/1202812988605/noticia/Noticia/Nuevo_refuerzo_para_el_Real_Madrid_C.htm Nuevo refuerzo para el Real Madrid C (New signing for Real Madrid C)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110915051434/http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/es/1202812988605/noticia/Noticia/Nuevo_refuerzo_para_el_Real_Madrid_C.htm|date=15 September 2011}}; Real Madrid CF, 18 February 2010 (in Spanish)</ref> During his four-month spell, he played just four [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] matches.\n\n===Gimn\u00e0stic===\nIn the summer of 2010, Rico signed with [[CF Pobla de Mafumet]] which acted as [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona]]'s [[farm team]], being first-choice with the fourth division side. In [[2010\u201311 Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|his first season]] he managed to be the former's third top scorer, behind [[Albert Virgili]] and [[Fran Carbi\u00e0]].\n\nOn 23 June 2011, Rico was promoted to ''N\u00e0stic'''s first team and signed a two-year contract.<ref>[http://www.nastictac.com/2011/06/julio-rico-pasa-a-ser-jugador-de-la-primera-plantilla-del-nastic/ Julio Rico pasa a ser jugador de la primera plantilla del N\u00e0stic (Julio Rico is now N\u00e0stic first-team player)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110702004803/http://www.nastictac.com/2011/06/julio-rico-pasa-a-ser-jugador-de-la-primera-plantilla-del-nastic/|date=2 July 2011}}; N\u00e0stic Tac, 23 June 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> On 10 July, he was officially presented with the [[Catalonia|Catalans]].<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2011/07/10/futbol/equipos/gimnastic/1310333141.html Julio Rico, presentado con el primer equipo (Julio Rico, presented with the first team)]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 10 July 2011 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nRico made his competitive debut with Gimn\u00e0stic on 6 August 2011, against [[RCD Espanyol]] for the season's [[Copa Catalunya]], coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] [[Berry Powel]] in the 64th minute of a 1\u20132 loss.<ref>[http://www.rcdespanyol.com/principal.php?modulo=detalleNoticia&idnoticia=11650&idseccion=28&idsite=1&idmenu=9&idsubmenu=108 2\u20131: Finalistes (2\u20131: Finalists)]; RCD Espanyol, 6 August 2011 (in Catalan)</ref> He made his first [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] appearance on 4 September, replacing [[Eloy Gila|Eloy]] in a 0\u20130 draw at [[CD Numancia]];<ref>[http://www.gimnasticdetarragona.com/cat2/es/act-noticia.php?id=4024 Numancia 0\u20130 N\u00e0stic]; Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona, 4 September 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> after only two league appearances (three overall) with the main squad, he was loaned to [[RCD Espanyol B]].<ref>[http://www.manquepierda.com/blog/el-ex-canterano-julio-rico-cedido-al-espanol-b-conoce-mas-sobre-el/ El ex canterano Julio Rico, cedido al Espa\u00f1ol B. Conoce m\u00e1s sobre \u00e9l (Former youth player Julio Rico, loaned to Espa\u00f1ol B. Learn more about him)]; Manquepierda, 31 January 2012 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\n===Journeyman===\nRico had his contract with Gimn\u00e0stic terminated on 31 August 2012.<ref>[http://www.gimnasticdetarragona.com/cat2/es/act-noticia.php?id=4953 El N\u00e0stic y Julio Rico rescinden el contrato (N\u00e0stic and Julio Rico terminate contract)]; Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona, 31 August 2012 (in Spanish)</ref> On the same day, he signed with [[CE L'Hospitalet]] also of the third level,<ref>[http://lasegundabarrabajab.blogspot.com.br/2012/08/julio-rico-ficha-por-el-hospitalet_31.html Julio Rico ficha por el Hospitalet (Julio Rico signs for Hospitalet)]; La Segunda B, 31 August 2012 (in Spanish)</ref> and on 20 August of the following year he joined fellow league club [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]].<ref>[http://www.todomercadoweb.es/mercado-futbolistico/oficial-cultural-leonesa-llega-julio-rico-54573 Oficial: Cultural Leonesa, llega Julio Rico (Official: Cultural Leonesa, Julio Rico arrives)]; Todo Mercado Web, 20 August 2013 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nOn 2 July 2014, Rico moved to [[UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s]] still in the third tier.<ref>[http://uniondeportivalogro\u00f1es.com/index.php/8-destacados/668-el-defensa-lateral-julio-rico-nuevo-jugador-de-la-ud-logrones El defensa lateral Julio Rico, nuevo jugador de la UD. Logro\u00f1\u00e9s (Full back Julio Rico, new player of UD. Logro\u00f1\u00e9s)]; UD Logro\u00f1\u00e9s, 2 July 2014 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|400380}}\n*{{Futbolme profile|7085}}\n*{{LaPreferente|27613}}\n*[http://beticopedia.blogspot.com/2011/07/julio-rico.html Stats at Beticopedia] {{in lang|es}}\n*{{Soccerway|julio-alberto-rico-pardillo/205479}}\n\n{{Burgos CF squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rico, Julio}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Sierra Sur (Seville)]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Andalusian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Betis Deportivo Balompi\u00e9 footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid C footballers]]\n[[Category:C